        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 9:10PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 910 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 15 miles west of Big Sandy to 15 miles south of
St. Pierre. Movement was northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Big Sandy, Azure, Parker School, Agency, St. Pierre, Gildford,
Sangrey, Boneau, Box Elder, Hingham, Rudyard, Rocky Boy, Laredo,
Kenilworth, and Kremlin.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM MDT for
north central Montana.</instruction>
